 After several residents have complained about the bad odour hanging over the town, DA Councillor Johann Dyason has opened up an investigation. Dyason contacted the Department of Water and Sanitation and they took water samples from the river, he is currently waiting for the results.
In the meantime, the councillor has reported blocked manholes to the Steve Tshwete Local Municipality. Councillor Dyason shows the Middelburg Observer a manhole that has been leaking on multiple occasions over the last couple of months. The municipality has been battling to unclog the responsible sewer line that runs along the marsh behind the Middelburg SPCA. www.mobserver.co.za is currently investigating businesses in the industrial area that flush waste water into the sewer lines.
